<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-05-07T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-05-07T17:00:00-05:00" n="479" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d479">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/6625: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-05-07T18:00:00-04:00">May 7, 1934—6
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>139. Please inform Canton in reference to its telegram of April 29,
                                noon,<note n="24" xml:id="d479fn24"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>,
                                    <ref target="#pg_147">p. 147</ref>.</note> as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>In your discretion, you are authorized, on some opportune
                                    occasion when you are discussing with members of the Southwest
                                    Political Council and other officials at Canton the oil
                                    discrimination matter or <pb facs="0656" n="566" xml:id="pg_566"/> other cases of discriminatory treatment of Americans at
                                    Canton, to refer to the declaration made by the Southwest
                                    Political Council on April 27 and to remind them of their
                                    obligation to observe treaties between China and the foreign
                                    powers.</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>